# Migration and Deprecation Safety

## Must
- Guard high-risk migrations behind feature flags where feasible.
- Validate old/new paths in parallel for critical transitions until equivalence is demonstrated.
- Record deprecations with removal timeline and replacement contract.
- Document rollback strategy for migration PRs affecting core contracts.

## Must Not
- Do not remove legacy path before replacement passes required validation matrix.
- Do not merge migration-only shortcuts without a closure plan.

## Required Evidence
- Dual-path comparison report and migration closure checklist.
